    {
      "id": "hskNkeTT6GLNyyz-YW4dl",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 392,
      "y": 1026,
      "width": 884.6595458984375,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1971c2",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aY",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 42275796,
      "version": 226,
      "versionNonce": 575769405,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1782310027866,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "    Defn:- It allows an object to pass a request along a chain of potential handlers. Each \nhandler in chain decides either to process the request or pass it to the next handler.",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "    Defn:- It allows an object to pass a request along a chain of potential handlers. Each \nhandler in chain decides either to process the request or pass it to the next handler.",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "lV9IcOu9C8-jgEzzVgOIA",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 394,
      "y": 1127,
      "width": 1119.1793212890625,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aZ",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1015848940,
      "version": 299,
      "versionNonce": 781606124,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776791750672,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "LL vs COR :- COR is diffrent than LL as its intend is to handle the request, also linked list points only single \nclass Node* next, but here COR it points to type of node like it can be ConcreatHandler1 or ConcreatHandler2 etc",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "LL vs COR :- COR is diffrent than LL as its intend is to handle the request, also linked list points only single \nclass Node* next, but here COR it points to type of node like it can be ConcreatHandler1 or ConcreatHandler2 etc",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "xbkN56PQhbCK5bjCvnN6v",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 382.1999816894531,
      "y": 1226,
      "width": 1053.9993896484375,
      "height": 50,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "aa",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 434671468,
      "version": 296,
      "versionNonce": 150807892,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1776791886956,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Use Case :- Standard Problem is Logger - Logging system,  LEave request  system - chain wala, Wherever\nwe have multiple chained hierarchy ki if one will full fill the request if itcant it will pass it to next like this...",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Use Case :- Standard Problem is Logger - Logging system,  LEave request  system - chain wala, Wherever\nwe have multiple chained hierarchy ki if one will full fill the request if itcant it will pass it to next like this...",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
